    "text": "In Florida, in Fort Lauderdale. It was taken at Hanukkah time, as the menorah shows-- on the last day of Hanukkah in 1994. From left to right-- lighting the candle or holding it is Christopher, Christopher Robin. Next to him is Corey, Corey Alexander. Next to him is Karen-- his mother, my daughter. Next to her is her father-- Teofil Cadmon, my ex-husband. Next to him is Karen's husband, [? Victor ?] Mantell, holding the boy lighting the candle really. And the boy lighting the candle with a kopl on is Daniel, Daniel Oliver. And the super-imposed on top little baby, who was still not in existence there, but who is now-- thank God. That's the baby girl, Kaelin. And she is now seven month old-- or young. [LAUGHS] This-- these two photographs are purely of baby Kaelin and myself when she and her mother, my daughter Karen, visited us here last month because my mother and I cannot go and visit them. So she brought the baby to introduce her to us. We didn't know her. She was then six months old. It's taken in this home here. This is my mother now. This was taken last month, which is in April 1996, in her ailing state, unfortunately, in her home. And the bottom photograph is of my mother enjoying the baby and the baby enjoying everything-- [LAUGHS] smiling all the time. That's it-- baby Kaelin. This photograph is of Peter, whom I mentioned before. This is Peter and myself. His name is Peter Janson-Smith-- spelled J-A-N-S-O-N, hyphen, Smith.",
